.LONG TERM...
Issued at 158 AM PDT Mon Jul 20 2026
(Tuesday through Sunday)

With generally decreasing 500 mb positive vorticity Monday this
will help keep convective potential at a minimum with exception of
the North Bay Monday afternoon to early evening when there may be
a brief uptick in positive vorticity. However, even the 00z NAM
output for this timeframe shows minimal convective potential along
with convective inhibition. The HRRR, RRFS and GFS show essentially
no convective potential.

For Tuesday, 500 mb positive vorticity is essentially non-existant
including in the 00z NAM cross sections. Residual mid to high level
clouds may still be around, but there`ll likely won`t be a lifting
mechanism left to destabilize an atmospheric layer or air parcels.
The westerlies, wind shear and drier air is destructive to tropical
origin convective development, but there can be the exception to
this when a steep east to west moisture gradient helps temporarily
destabilize a lifted layer or air parcels. Given model trends and
further dissipation of TS Elida, this is unlikely Tuesday when the
tail end of the moisture gradient moves across the forecast area.
Stay tuned to the latest updates.

Otherwise it`ll be summertime dry weather, warm to hot inland and
coolest at the coast and bays mid to late week. The high pressure
system over the interior west will gradually shift southward then
slowly move to the Four Corners by the weekend.

