.AVIATION...
(18Z TAFS)
Issued at 1049 AM PDT Mon Jul 20 2026

Mid to high level clouds continue to stream across the region from
the southwest this morning. These clouds helped eroding the
stratus deck below with most terminals having scattered out at
this hour. Showers accompanying these mid/high clouds may produce
a shower here and there however most will not hit the ground and
fall as virga. VFR conditions and diurnal winds will prevail
this afternoon. High confidence in the return of IFR conditions to
coastal terminals tonight with low confidence elsewhere due to
the shallow nature of the marine layer.

Vicinity of SFO...VFR conditions and northwesterly flow will
prevail. Low confidence on the return of an IFR cigs tonight,
however current thinking brings IFR cigs in around 05z over KOAK
and between 13z-17z over KSFO.


SFO Bridge Approach...Similar to SFO.

Monterey Bay Terminals...VFR conditions will prevail with
moderate northwesterly winds kicking in by this afternoon.
Moderate to high confidence on IFR cigs returning tonight.
Current thinking has IFR cigs returning around 02z.

