.MARINE...
(Today through Saturday)
Issued at 1049 AM PDT Mon Jul 20 2026

Light to locally moderate northwesterly winds will prevail
through midweek, becoming moderate Thursday into Friday. Slight
to moderate seas will prevail. Tropical cyclone activity in the
Eastern Pacific Ocean will spur several rounds of moderate period
southerly swells; hazardous conditions from mixed seas may result.
Instability from the remnants of the tropical cyclone will also
bring a slight chance of convection that may bring showers as well
as gusty and erratic outflow winds that would be result in
hazardous conditions to small craft.


